<subSubSection id="6EF16510FF86FFABF7FD277AFD90FA62" pageId="4" pageNumber="255" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="2654369BFF86FFABF7FD277AFD90FA62" blockId="4.[169,1228,1304,1651]" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">
<emphasis id="149FEA89FF86FFABF7FD277AFEA7FAE3" bold="true" box="[222,352,1368,1394]" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Posterior notopleural seta black, femora black (
<figureCitation id="BED02A1EFF86FFABF48B277AFBE3FAE2" box="[936,1060,1368,1395]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[174,207,1204,1226]" captionTargetBox="[363,1124,167,1191]" captionTargetId="figure-369@5.[348,1124,153,1205]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 21–26. C. misella. 21 — Ơ, habitus, left; 22 — mesonotum, dorsally; 23 — wing (SIZK); 24 — aculeus, ventrally; 25 — same, enlarged (SMNC); 26 — head (SIZK)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452434" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452434/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">fig. 21–22</figureCitation>
); Stigma with one hyaline spot; cell br with 2 hyaline spots (
<figureCitation id="BED02A1EFF86FFABF5EA275AFCD1FA02" box="[713,790,1400,1427]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[174,207,1204,1226]" captionTargetBox="[363,1124,167,1191]" captionTargetId="figure-369@5.[348,1124,153,1205]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 21–26. C. misella. 21 — Ơ, habitus, left; 22 — mesonotum, dorsally; 23 — wing (SIZK); 24 — aculeus, ventrally; 25 — same, enlarged (SMNC); 26 — head (SIZK)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452434" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452434/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">fig. 23</figureCitation>
); Ventral margin of the head shorter than head height (
<figureCitation id="BED02A1EFF86FFABF6A627BAFE13FA22" box="[389,468,1432,1459]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[174,207,1204,1226]" captionTargetBox="[363,1124,167,1191]" captionTargetId="figure-369@5.[348,1124,153,1205]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 21–26. C. misella. 21 — Ơ, habitus, left; 22 — mesonotum, dorsally; 23 — wing (SIZK); 24 — aculeus, ventrally; 25 — same, enlarged (SMNC); 26 — head (SIZK)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452434" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452434/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">fig. 26</figureCitation>
); Mesonotum with three brownish longitudinal bands (
<figureCitation id="BED02A1EFF86FFABF34C27BAFB79FA22" box="[1135,1214,1432,1459]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[174,207,1204,1226]" captionTargetBox="[363,1124,167,1191]" captionTargetId="figure-369@5.[348,1124,153,1205]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 21–26. C. misella. 21 — Ơ, habitus, left; 22 — mesonotum, dorsally; 23 — wing (SIZK); 24 — aculeus, ventrally; 25 — same, enlarged (SMNC); 26 — head (SIZK)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452434" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452434/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">fig. 22</figureCitation>
). Oviscape shorter than 4 posteriormost preabdominal tergites; apex of aculeus with one pair of not very prominent steps (
<figureCitation id="BED02A1EFF86FFABF6DE27FAFD8DFA62" box="[509,586,1496,1523]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[174,207,1204,1226]" captionTargetBox="[363,1124,167,1191]" captionTargetId="figure-369@5.[348,1124,153,1205]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 21–26. C. misella. 21 — Ơ, habitus, left; 22 — mesonotum, dorsally; 23 — wing (SIZK); 24 — aculeus, ventrally; 25 — same, enlarged (SMNC); 26 — head (SIZK)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452434" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452434/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">fig. 25</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6EF16510FF86FFABF7FD27DAFC21F9E2" pageId="4" pageNumber="255" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="2654369BFF86FFABF7FD27DAFC21F9E2" blockId="4.[169,1228,1304,1651]" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">
<emphasis id="149FEA89FF86FFABF7FD27DAFEAAF983" bold="true" box="[222,365,1528,1554]" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">Comments.</emphasis>
This species is common throughout Palaearctics, from Europe to 
<collectingCountry id="5EFC760BFF86FFABF35E27DAFB00F983" box="[1149,1223,1528,1554]" name="China" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">China</collectingCountry>
, but very local in 
<collectingCountry id="5EFC760BFF86FFABF6A3243BFE72F9A2" box="[384,437,1561,1587]" name="Iran" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">Iran</collectingCountry>
. Larvae feed in flower heads of various wormwoods, first of all, mugwort and absinth (
<taxonomicName id="E1EB4D18FF86FFABF6E3241BFD50F9C3" box="[448,663,1592,1619]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Artemisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="4" pageNumber="255" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulgaris">
<emphasis id="149FEA89FF86FFABF6E3241BFD50F9C3" box="[448,663,1592,1619]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">Artemisia vulgaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L., 
<taxonomicName id="E1EB4D18FF86FFABF5EB241BFC95F9C3" box="[712,850,1592,1619]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Artemisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="4" pageNumber="255" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="absinthii">
<emphasis id="149FEA89FF86FFABF5EB241BFC95F9C3" box="[712,850,1592,1619]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">A. absinthii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L.), which occur mainly in the North-Western and Northern 
<collectingCountry id="5EFC760BFF86FFABF533247BFD82F9E2" box="[528,581,1625,1651]" name="Iran" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">Iran</collectingCountry>
. See also comments on 
<taxonomicName id="E1EB4D18FF86FFABF47A247BFC18F9E3" box="[857,991,1624,1651]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Artemisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="4" pageNumber="255" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="absinthii">
<emphasis id="149FEA89FF86FFABF47A247BFC18F9E3" box="[857,991,1624,1651]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">C. absinthii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
